G. A former member of the senate, except one who is a registered lobbyist,
may enter those portions of the Senate Floor designated as Sections B, C, and D, the Senate
Library, the office of the secretary, and that portion of the floor behind the Secretary's desk.
H. No person shall wear eyeglasses that have video or audio recording
capabilities inside the Senate Chamber without the express permission of the President
of the Senate.
